Description: KDE-like activities manager for GNOME
 GNOME Activities Manager provides KDE-activities-like task management
 for the GNOME desktop environment. It allows users to create named
 activities/tasks, each with their own set of applications and files.
 .
 Features:
  - Create, delete, and switch between activities
  - Automatically open/close apps when switching activities
  - Track open files per activity
  - Firefox extension for tab tracking
  - Always-available apps (e.g. Thunderbird) across all activities
